<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="109" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName LSID="708CDDDC-9991-58BB-9848-A8FCE0929D65" authority="Alloptes Canestrini, 1879" authorityName="Alloptes Canestrini" authorityYear="1879" class="Arachnida" family="Alloptidae" genus="Alloptes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Alloptes (Alloptes)" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Alloptes">Alloptes Alloptes Canestrini, 1879</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="109" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
The subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Alloptes" authorityName="Alloptes Canestrini" authorityYear="1879" class="Arachnida" family="Alloptidae" genus="Alloptes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Alloptes (Alloptes)" order="Charadriiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Alloptes">Alloptes Alloptes</taxonomicName>
s. str. currently includes three species and is characterized by the following features (
<bibRefCitation author="Gaud, J" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de l'Institut scientifique de Madagascar, Series A" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="161 - 166" refId="B12" refString="Gaud, J, 1952. Acariens plumicoles (Analgesidae) de quelques oiseaux des Iles Kerguelen (Recolte P. Paulian). Memoires de l'Institut scientifique de Madagascar, Series A 7: 161 - 166" title="Acariens plumicoles (Analgesidae) de quelques oiseaux des Iles Kerguelen (Recolte P. Paulian)." volume="7" year="1952">Gaud 1952</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gaud, J" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe des Sciences naturelles et physiques du Maroc" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" refId="B14" refString="Gaud, J, 1972. Acariens sarcoptiformes plumicoles (Analgoidea): parasites sur les oiseaux charadriiformes d'Afrique. Annales du Musee royale de l'Afrique centrale, Serie in-8o, Sciences zoologiques 193: 1-116." title="Acariens sarcoptiformes plumicoles (Analgoidea): parasites sur les oiseaux charadriiformes d'Afrique. Annales du Musee royale de l'Afrique centrale, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences zoologiques 193: 1 - 116." year="1972">1972</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mironov, SV" journalOrPublisher="Parazitologiya" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="216 - 222" refId="B28" refString="Mironov, SV, 1996. On a validity of the genus Plicatalloptes (Acarina: Analgoidea: Alloptidae). Parazitologiya 30: 216 - 222" title="On a validity of the genus Plicatalloptes (Acarina: Analgoidea: Alloptidae)." volume="30" year="1996">Mironov 1996</bibRefCitation>
): in both sexes, seta 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">mG</emphasis>
of genu II is spiculiform; in males, the opisthosoma is roughly shaped as an equilateral triangle with terminal part strongly enlarged, setae 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">h3</emphasis>
are present, setae 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">ps2</emphasis>
are well developed (half as long as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">f2</emphasis>
); in females, the opisthosoma is rounded, the opisthosomal lobes are not developed, idiosomal setae 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">ps1</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">f2</emphasis>
are present. Representatives of the subgenus are known from birds of the families 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" class="Aves" family="Scolopacidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Charadriiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Scolopacidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lesson" authorityYear="1828" class="Aves" family="Chionidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Charadriiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Chionidae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gaud, J" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de l'Institut scientifique de Madagascar, Series A" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="161 - 166" refId="B12" refString="Gaud, J, 1952. Acariens plumicoles (Analgesidae) de quelques oiseaux des Iles Kerguelen (Recolte P. Paulian). Memoires de l'Institut scientifique de Madagascar, Series A 7: 161 - 166" title="Acariens plumicoles (Analgesidae) de quelques oiseaux des Iles Kerguelen (Recolte P. Paulian)." volume="7" year="1952">Gaud 1952</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gaud, J" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe des Sciences naturelles et physiques du Maroc" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="105 - 136" refId="B13" refString="Gaud, J, 1957. Acariens plumicoles (Analgesoidea) parasites des oiseaux du Maroc. I. Proctophyllodidae. Bulletin de la Societe des Sciences naturelles et physiques du Maroc 37: 105 - 136" title="Acariens plumicoles (Analgesoidea) parasites des oiseaux du Maroc. I. Proctophyllodidae." volume="37" year="1957">1957</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gaud, J" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe des Sciences naturelles et physiques du Maroc" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" refId="B14" refString="Gaud, J, 1972. Acariens sarcoptiformes plumicoles (Analgoidea): parasites sur les oiseaux charadriiformes d'Afrique. Annales du Musee royale de l'Afrique centrale, Serie in-8o, Sciences zoologiques 193: 1-116." title="Acariens sarcoptiformes plumicoles (Analgoidea): parasites sur les oiseaux charadriiformes d'Afrique. Annales du Musee royale de l'Afrique centrale, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences zoologiques 193: 1 - 116." year="1972">1972</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vasyukova, TT" journalOrPublisher="Publisher: Nauka, Siberian Dept, Novosibirsk" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" refId="B46" refString="Vasyukova, TT, Mironov, SV, 1991. Feather mites of Anseriformes and Charadriiformes of Yakutia. Systematics. Publisher: Nauka, Siberian Dept, Novosibirsk" title="Feather mites of Anseriformes and Charadriiformes of Yakutia. Systematics." year="1991">Vasyukova and Mironov 1991</bibRefCitation>
). Five 
<taxonomicName authority="Canestrini, 1879" authorityName="Canestrini" authorityYear="1879" class="Arachnida" family="Alloptidae" genus="Alloptes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Alloptes" order="Charadriiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Alloptes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dubinin, VB" journalOrPublisher="Trudy Zoologicheskogo Instituta AN SSSR" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="251 - 268" refId="B10" refString="Dubinin, VB, 1952. Feather mites of birds of Wrangel Island. Trudy Zoologicheskogo Instituta AN SSSR 12: 251 - 268" title="Feather mites of birds of Wrangel Island." volume="12" year="1952">Dubinin (1952)</bibRefCitation>
from auks (
<taxonomicName class="Aves" family="Alcidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Charadriiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Alcidae</taxonomicName>
) could also belong to this subgenus, because these mites have filiform genual setae 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">mG</emphasis>
II and females have the opisthosoma rounded or with strongly abbreviated lobes, but all these species need re-investigation.
</paragraph>
